<div class='row t20 b1'>
  <div class='medium-4 columns'><b>Preview:</b></div>
  <div class='medium-8 columns'><div class="webex-group">
<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>Given two points <span class="math inline">\(p = (2, 4)\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q = (4, 4)\)</span> in a Cartesian coordinate system:</p>
<p>What is the Manhattan distance <span class="math inline">\(d_1(p, q)\)</span>? <input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-a6dc1014d128167a298e6794b5cc79a6' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='OhRWQWw='/></p>
<p>What is the Euclidean distance <span class="math inline">\(d_2(p, q)\)</span>? <input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-fbe992176293b0d20c7f084518e2374c' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='PUBXG2Q='/></p>
<p>What is the maximum distance <span class="math inline">\(d_\infty(p, q)\)</span>? <input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-7e55b772a8c6270fd87a3668c7ceea5c' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='bEcHFz8='/></p>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<p>The distances are visualized below in green (<span class="math inline">\(d_1\)</span>), red (<span class="math inline">\(d_2\)</span>), and blue (<span class="math inline">\(d_\infty\)</span>).</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
<ul>
<li><span class="math inline">\(d_1(p, q) = \sum_i |p_i - q_i| = |2 - 4| + |4 - 4| = 2\)</span>.</li>
<li><span class="math inline">\(d_2(p, q) = \sqrt{\sum_i (p_i - q_i)^2} = \sqrt{(2 - 4)^2 + (4 - 4)^2} = 2\)</span>.</li>
<li><span class="math inline">\(d_\infty(p, q) = \max_i |p_i - q_i| = \max(|2 - 4|, |4 - 4|) = 2\)</span>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>Given two points <span class="math inline">\(p = (3, 2)\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q = (5, 5)\)</span> in a Cartesian coordinate system:</p>
<p>What is the Manhattan distance <span class="math inline">\(d_1(p, q)\)</span>? <input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-045f434a521d3b47cfe9d2d960da44d0' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='axYARGk='/></p>
<p>What is the Euclidean distance <span class="math inline">\(d_2(p, q)\)</span>? <input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-aaa6dbc7ce5e1bd16f5631827090f32d' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='OkNSGFJSVRU+'/></p>
<p>What is the maximum distance <span class="math inline">\(d_\infty(p, q)\)</span>? <input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-a2895e25ccb57219b484703a0c72a6f7' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='OhALG2g='/></p>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<p>The distances are visualized below in green (<span class="math inline">\(d_1\)</span>), red (<span class="math inline">\(d_2\)</span>), and blue (<span class="math inline">\(d_\infty\)</span>).</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
<ul>
<li><span class="math inline">\(d_1(p, q) = \sum_i |p_i - q_i| = |3 - 5| + |2 - 5| = 5\)</span>.</li>
<li><span class="math inline">\(d_2(p, q) = \sqrt{\sum_i (p_i - q_i)^2} = \sqrt{(3 - 5)^2 + (2 - 5)^2} = 3.606\)</span>.</li>
<li><span class="math inline">\(d_\infty(p, q) = \max_i |p_i - q_i| = \max(|3 - 5|, |2 - 5|) = 3\)</span>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>Given two points <span class="math inline">\(p = (3, 2)\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q = (4, 1)\)</span> in a Cartesian coordinate system:</p>
<p>What is the Manhattan distance <span class="math inline">\(d_1(p, q)\)</span>? <input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-d6988786f0aa2a6d39577bc106845f08' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='PxQLGmU='/></p>
<p>What is the Euclidean distance <span class="math inline">\(d_2(p, q)\)</span>? <input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-7bc86e5906b796d29259a77ff354b552' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='bEBSFgJUARtt'/></p>
<p>What is the maximum distance <span class="math inline">\(d_\infty(p, q)\)</span>? <input class='webex-solveme nospaces' id='webex-369b0df160dc364c4b336fede9dc4141' data-tol='0.01' size='20' data-answer='aBQIQG0='/></p>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<p>The distances are visualized below in green (<span class="math inline">\(d_1\)</span>), red (<span class="math inline">\(d_2\)</span>), and blue (<span class="math inline">\(d_\infty\)</span>).</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
<ul>
<li><span class="math inline">\(d_1(p, q) = \sum_i |p_i - q_i| = |3 - 4| + |2 - 1| = 2\)</span>.</li>
<li><span class="math inline">\(d_2(p, q) = \sqrt{\sum_i (p_i - q_i)^2} = \sqrt{(3 - 4)^2 + (2 - 1)^2} = 1.414\)</span>.</li>
<li><span class="math inline">\(d_\infty(p, q) = \max_i |p_i - q_i| = \max(|3 - 4|, |2 - 1|) = 1\)</span>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>
